scripts.comment: Here is an example program created with the block. Can you figure out the prime numbers multiplied together? Factoring the product of (large) prime numbers is actually key in many encryption techniques!

The Sieve of Eratosthenes is an algorithm for determining prime numbers. In this algorithm, you have a list of numbers up to some limit that you will cross out (or set to "false") if they are not prime. By definition, 1 is not considered prime and will be crossed out. For every number still considered prime, we will "cross out" all multiples until we reach the limit (or half the limit since it won't have any multiples in the range!).
